 in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Folmar II. von Blieskastel was born in 1150, his father, Folmar I. von Blieskastel, was 19 and his mother, Clémence de Metz, was 37. He married Jutta von Saarbrücken. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1223, in Bavaria, Germany, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1150–1223":"1150–1223","1153–1223":"1153–1223","1180–1237":"1180–1237","1131–1179":"1131–1179","1113–1179":"1113–1179","1237":"1237","1179":"1179","1223":"1223","UM 1163":"umbes 1163","1113":"1113","vor 1223":"enne 1223","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1150":"1150","after 1179":"pärast 1179","1180":"1180","Bliescastel, Germany":"Saksamaa","Bavaria, Germany":"Bayern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1150–1223":"1150–1223","1153–1223":"1153–1223","1180–1237":"1180–1237","1131–1179":"1131–1179","1113–1179":"1113–1179","1237":"1237","1179":"1179","1223":"1223","UM 1163":"noin 1163","1113":"1113","vor 1223":"ennen vuotta 1223","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1150":"1150","after 1179":"1179 jälkeen","1180":"1180","Bliescastel, Germany":"Saksa","Bavaria, Germany":"Bayern, Saksa"},"fr":{"1150–1223":"1150–1223","1153–1223":"1153–1223","1180–1237":"1180–1237","1131–1179":"1131–1179","1113–1179":"1113–1179","1237":"1237","1179":"1179","1223":"1223","UM 1163":"environ 1163","1113":"1113","vor 1223":"avant 1223","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1150":"1150","after 1179":"après 1179","1180":"1180","Bliescastel, Germany":"Allemagne","Bavaria, Germany":"Bayern, Allemagne","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Folmar II. von Blieskastel est né en 1150, son père, Folmar I. von Blieskastel, avait 19 ans et sa mère, Cléme